  "text": "The Apache Kafka consumer group rebalance protocol implementation in the clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ directory is composed of nine Java source files containing classes with 'Rebalance' in their names. These classes are organized into two main categories: callback handlers and metrics managers.\n\nCallback Handlers (5 files):\n1. ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker.java) - Encapsulates invocation of ConsumerRebalanceListener callback methods (onPartitionsAssigned, onPartitionsRevoked, onPartitionsLost) with logging and metrics recording.\n2. ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName.java) - Enum providing static names for ConsumerRebalanceListener interface methods.\n3. StreamsRebalanceListener (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceListener.java) - Interface for handling Kafka Streams group rebalance events (onTasksRevoked, onTasksAssigned, onAllTasksLost).\n4. StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker.java) - Encapsulates invocation of StreamsRebalanceListener callback methods with error handling.\n5. StreamsRebalanceData (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceData.java) - Data structure holding information needed for Streams rebalance protocol participation, including process ID, endpoint info, subtopologies, and task assignments.\n\nMetrics Managers (4 files):\n1. RebalanceMetricsManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/RebalanceMetricsManager.java) - Abstract base class defining interface for rebalance metrics tracking with methods for recording rebalance start/end events.\n2. ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager.java) - Concrete implementation extending RebalanceMetricsManager to track consumer rebalance metrics including latency (avg/max/total), rebalance rate, and failed rebalance statistics.\n3. ShareRebalanceMetricsManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/ShareRebalanceMetricsManager.java) - Concrete implementation extending RebalanceMetricsManager for share consumer rebalance metrics tracking.\n4. RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager.java) - Tracks metrics for rebalance listener callback execution (partition revoked/assigned/lost latency measurements).\n\nThese classes work together to implement the consumer group rebalance protocol, managing callback invocation, state transitions, and performance metrics collection across both classic consumer group protocol and Kafka Streams group protocol implementations."
}

